  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "CPI came in as expected at 3.3% with core subdued, but energy prices showing massive spikes (fuel oil +44.2% Y/Y) while consumer sentiment collapsed to 47.6 vs 52.0 expected. Bitcoin rallied above $72K on the cooler inflation print, but rising inflation expectations (1-year up to 4.8% vs 3.8%) and energy shocks suggest stagflationary pressures building despite the headline relief.",
    "regimeImpact": "Bear market relief rally remains intact as CPI met expectations and yields stayed below 4.50%, but deteriorating consumer sentiment and spiking energy costs signal this rally may be fragile.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Maintain BMNR cash-secured put ladder as Bitcoin reclaimed $72K but watch $62,300 structural level closely",
      "Monitor oil prices for break above $100 stagflation threshold given fuel oil surge",
      "Consider reducing Maturity overweight exposure as consumer sentiment collapse suggests economic weakness ahead"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Consumer sentiment crashed to 47.6 vs 52.0 expected with inflation expectations spiking to 4.8% 1-year, signaling stagflation fears despite headline CPI relief.",
      "Energy showing massive price spikes with fuel oil up 44.2% Y/Y, approaching the $100 oil stagflation threshold.",
      "Bitcoin strength above $72K suggests risk-on sentiment but factory orders flat vs +0.4% expected shows underlying economic weakness.",
      "10Y yields holding near 4.3% below the 4.50% growth stress level keeps relief rally intact for now."
    ]
